import seaborn as sns
    import statsmodels.api as sm # for calculating statistics
    import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
    import pandas as pd
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    
    def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
        data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
        data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
        plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
        ax = sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.title('What is the trend of budget allocation over the years?', wrap=True)
        return plt;

    chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm # for calculating statistics
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median: {data["value"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm # for calculating statistics
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=data)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between budget and forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm # for calculating statistics
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data, estimator=lambda x: sum(x)/len(x))
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average budget allocation per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
